# Constitution

Hard limits for Playwright work in this repo. Details live in `playwright-conventions` and the skills below ‚Äî this file is the non-negotiable summary.

## MUST

| Rule | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Role-based locators | `getByRole` ‚Üí `getByLabel` ‚Üí `getByText`; `getByTestId` only as escape hatch. No CSS/XPath. |
| Web-first assertions | Wait with `expect(locator).‚Ä¶` / Playwright auto-waiting. Never fixed sleeps. |
| `storageState` auth | Log in once via the setup project; never per-test UI login. |
| Unique self-cleaning data | Unique names; track + API teardown (`trackProgram` / `api-cleanup`). No leftover records. |
| One tag per test | Exactly one of `@smoke` \| `@sanity` \| `@regression` \| `@api` \| `@e2e` \| `@destructive` on `test()` ‚Äî never on `describe`. `@destructive` only for shared/global state + serial + revert hook. |
| Reliability eval before Done | Orchestrator refreshes `eval-report.md` via `suite-reliability-eval` (flake, heal, generation-gate, ask-vs-guess) before marking Done / ending Backlog. |

## SHOULD

| Rule | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Faker factories | Build test data via Faker-backed factories, not hand-rolled literals. |
| Enums for repeated strings | Shared UI labels / statuses live in enums or constants ‚Äî no copy-paste magic strings. |
| JSDoc on action methods | Document POM / helper action methods (params, side effects, return). |

## WON'T

| Refusal | Do this instead |
|---------|-----------------|
| XPath (or CSS as default) | Re-discover via role / label / text. |
| `waitForTimeout` | Web-first `expect` or explicit Playwright waits. |
| Hardcoded secrets | `process.env` + existing auth fixtures. |
| `any` type | Proper Playwright / TypeScript types. |
| Weakened assertions | Fix app, locator, or triage ‚Äî never delete/`fixme` to green a red run. |
| Healing a real app bug | Route to `jira-bug-reporter` / `bug-reporter`; heal locators only for drift. |
| Tags on `describe` / multi-tag / wrong `@destructive` | One allowed tag on each `test()`; own-data cleanup keeps importance tag; shared-state needs `@destructive` + revert. |

## Agent governance

Behavioral contract (not hook-enforced). Audit before you edit; never invent facts.

### Audit-then-edit

For every **non-trivial** task, emit a **Proposal** block **before** any edit:

```
Proposal
- Scope: ‚Ä¶
- Confidence: N/10
- Rationale: ‚Ä¶
- Unknowns: ‚Ä¶
```

Trivial work (typo, one-line rename, pure formatting) may skip the Proposal. Everything else ‚Äî new files, multi-file changes, locator/API guesses, ticket implementation ‚Äî must propose first.

### Confidence gate

| Confidence | Action |
|------------|--------|
| **< 5** | Do **not** proceed. Ask for the missing input. |
| **5‚Äì7** | Proceed only with **explicit Unknowns** listed and **human approval**. |
| **‚â• 8** | Proceed. |

### Do not invent

Never invent a path, enum, env var, credential, or message. If it is not in the repo, ticket, or prior exploration ‚Äî **ask** or **explore** first.

